+## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S1-P03-T020 (500 Golden Set + content Release Gate; S1-P03 complete)
+
+- Twentieth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program and the last of S1-P03, one task per run. Goal: turn content quality into a continuously-acceptable release gate. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; a read-only D1 sample of 500 items (changed_db=False), no worker/D1 change. Per the Owner directive of 2026-07-16 the human rubric and P0 accuracy use a provisional_machine baseline pending an Owner spot-check. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: golden_set_500.json (a 500-sample index with P0 fields), GOLDEN_SET_RUBRIC.md (the human rubric for P0 facts / key-claim evidence / empty-template / language / fact-interpretation-inference with a scoring flow), tools/content_release_gate.py (the CI gate), and BEFORE_AFTER.md + benchmarks. Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S1-P03-T020/test-results/release_gate.txt): running the gate on the 500 render payloads returns RELEASE with key_unlocated 0 (key-claim evidence 100%), empty_or_template 0 (no empty section or template leak), and p0_fact_accuracy 1.0 (>= the 0.99 threshold; machine extraction fidelity, provisional pending human); an injected empty L0 with an unlocated key fact returns BLOCK_CONTENT_BUNDLE with scope content_bundle, so a failure blocks only the content bundle and not the deploy. Before/after: the raw 500 items were 460/500 defective (english_direct_output 361/500), and after the S1-P03 contract the content bundle passes the gate. This completes S1-P03 end to end: factsheet extraction (T016) -> defect baseline (T017) -> L0-L3 人话版 + evidence locator (T018) -> QA/retry/fallback (T019) -> Golden Set + Release Gate (T020). Cost (unknown != 0): 1 read-only D1 SELECT, D1 rows_read about 500, D1 written 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S1-P03-T019 (content QA + single retry + factsheet fallback)
 
 - Nineteenth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S1-P03), one task per run. Goal: on a generation failure, prefer to say less rather than publish template garbage. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; reuses the T018 render payload, no worker/D1 change and no model call (a self-test stub simulates generation). Deliverable under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: tools/content_qa.py (five QA checks -- language large-English, empty, duplicate, unsupported (a claim without an evidence locator), and template boilerplate -- plus publish() with at most one retry and fallback() which quarantines L2 and publishes only the fact card L0/L1 + raw evidence L3). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S1-P03-T019/test-results/qa_tests.txt) at 5/5 PASS: injecting a model timeout falls back after at most one retry (initial + 1) to publish_mode fact_card_and_raw_only; injecting template garbage or a missing-field stub fails QA and falls back; a duplicate L2 falls back; a valid generation publishes in full in a single attempt; and the baseline payload has no unsupported claims. This seals the english_direct_output/template defects on the publish path. Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls at most 2 per item (controlled by publish()). Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
